Package com.github.tommyettinger.crux

Interface Point3<P extends Point3<P>>

Type Parameters:
P - in implementing types, this is the implementing type
All Superinterfaces:
PointN<P>
public interface Point3<P extends Point3<P>> extends PointN<P>
A minimal super-interface that can be implemented by 3D PointN types, such as (subclasses of) com.badlogic.gdx.math.GridPoint3 and com.badlogic.gdx.math.Vector3.

    • x

      P x(float next)
      Sets the first (x) coordinate to next. Always takes a float, even if PointN.floatingPoint() is false. For mutable types, this should edit this value in-place. For immutable types, it must return a new value.
      Parameters:
      next - the new value for the first (x) coordinate
      Returns:
      if this is mutable, then this value after editing; if this is immutable, then a different edited point
